re than 2,000 people=E2=80=A6Shopify soared about 27% to C$79.76 as of 10:3=
5 a.m. in Toronto, the biggest intraday rise since 2015.

The logistics deal is a big change for the Canadian e-commerce giant, rever=
sing a strategy it had implemented to better compete with Amazon.com Inc. F=
lexport will acquire most of its fulfillment assets including those of ship=
ping startup Deliverr Inc., which Shopify bought just last year for $2.1 bi=
llion=E2=80=A6

Revenue for the period came in at $1.51 billion, beating the $1.43 billion =
average estimate of analysts surveyed by Bloomberg. Gross merchandise volum=
e, the total value of merchant sales across Shopify=E2=80=99s platforms, wa=
